	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=174515><span id=Scholar>Angelys</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>105 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.02]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The white pelts you get are for a newbie armour quest in Halas.&nbsp;&nbsp;You give them to the woman in Mac's Kilts and in return she gives you a piece of armour.  It's good stuff for a newbie (I did it at level 4) and it changes your appearance as well.<br>However, I'd imagine that if you're a Dark Elf who's come this far then you're either going to be too high level for the quest to be useful, or you're going to be KoS in Halas.<br><br>As for the defined quality pelts, I'm not sure yet what you can use them for.  I usually just sell them to vendors.  You could always practice your Tailoring skill, as Everfrost has an abundance of bears (for the pelts) and spiders (for the silk thread).  In fact, of all the places I've been so far, Everfrost seems to be the best place for tailors.  Of course, I don't have Luclin or PoP yet.<br><br>Hope this helps!</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=513304 target=akztarg><b><span style='color: black;'>Dajmin</b></span style='color: black;'></a><span style='color: maroon;'><b> [69 DE Dread Lord]</b></span style='color: maroon;'><br><b>Greenmist</b>: 16 June 04<br>"Nerf it until it stops moving, then steal it's wallet"</td></tr>
